OL,3,CCouriers march into Royal Mail building
OL,5,FThey say they currently have to cover
OL,6,Fall of their travel costs, such as
OL,7,Fupkeeping their bikes and paying for
OL,8,Fnew ones when needed with the union
OL,9,Falso saying some of the workers take
OL,10,Fless than the minimum wage annually
OL,11,Fafter they have covered their travel
OL,12,Fcosts.
OL,14,FOne of the couriers, spoke of her
OL,15,Fexperience saying: "There is a very
OL,16,Ftoxic environment, sometimes we have
OL,17,Fpeople who call us up and say 'you
OL,18,Fhave to do this work,' when I say I'm
OL,19,Fon my lunch break, they say 'I tell
OL,20,Fyou when you can stop'.
